stories.text:
This popular discussion was killed today. https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=30058807 It wasn't a productive discussion. But it wasn't off topic and didn't violate the https://news.ycombinator.com/newsguidelines.html as a submission as far as I can tell. Perhaps the guidelines could be updated or someone could explain why it got killed?

There is a lot of powerful people who'd want negative press around web3/crypto killed. A16Z et al for example. It feels a bit icky to be left wondering why something got killed without explanation.

stories.text: I routinely want to revisit clicked links on hacker news. The gray color of clicked links is too close to the color of the details and causes me to always (without fail) scroll past the link of interest. To me, it is by far the most frustrating thing about the website.
